Class LinkedBag<T>

java.lang.Object
LinkedBag<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
BagInterface<T>
public class LinkedBag<T> extends Object implements BagInterface<T>
This is the LinkedBag class which implements the BagInterface interface. With this class, we can create Bags (unordered lists which allow duplicates), find the union, intersection, and difference of two bags. The bag is implemented using a linked chain of Nodes. Each method is documented separately.
Version:
2.0
Author:
Pierlorenzo Peruzzo
